<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="165" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,152,827]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,765,791]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is from Latin 
<emphasis box="[697,762,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">hirtus</emphasis>
= “bristling with thorns”, and refers to characteristic feature of transtilla.
</paragraph>
